President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Hawaii due to severe storms, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from September 11-14, 2016. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Dr. Ahsha N. Tribble has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.